{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"E4tHh7Kq6jlwGiNAjAJZO","title":"Scalability","desc":"","updated":1643537071396,"created":1643534154250,"custom":{},"fname":"data-system-fundamentals.scalability","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"9518be2228ac01f3f1c4596fa6931e0c","links":[{"from":{"fname":"data-system-fundamentals","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":80,"offset":80},"end":{"line":2,"column":131,"offset":131},"indent":[]},"value":"data-system-fundamentals.scalability","alias":"scalable"}],"anchors":{"describing-load":{"type":"header","text":"Describing Load","value":"describing-load","line":10,"column":0,"depth":2},"describing-performance":{"type":"header","text":"Describing Performance","value":"describing-performance","line":19,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"aYiQhcOPTZlphrGiOEnrY","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"scalability\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#scalability\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Scalability</h1>\n<p>If we increase the number of users or amount of data that passes through the system, how do we add additional computing power to cope with the load?</p>\n<h2 id=\"describing-load\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#describing-load\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Describing Load</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>What are your system's <em>load parameters</em>? (e.g. DB read/write ratio, concurrent connections, bandwidth usage, whale users, etc.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>e.g. Twitter home page. </p>\n<ul>\n<li>A user can follow many people. When user goes to home page, fetch all recent tweets of followees from DB. Problem: DB reads expensive.</li>\n<li>Solution: cache a user's home page. When followee tweets, update followers' caches. Problem: Celebrities have many followers. Tweets are expensive as they need to update millions of cache entries.</li>\n<li>Solution: Use both. Don't update cache for whale followees. If user follows a whale user, fetch from DB to get update from them.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"describing-performance\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#describing-performance\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Describing Performance</h2>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/system-design-notes/notes/aYiQhcOPTZlphrGiOEnrY\">Data System Fundamentals</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"kQo4KQYN6t85wemYmxivg","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1643530277910,"created":1643530277910,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"fdd93fd3e598fcac91501a37e7e54663","links":[],"anchors":{"welcome-to-dendron":{"type":"header","text":"Welcome to Dendron","value":"welcome-to-dendron","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1},"lookup":{"type":"header","text":"Lookup","value":"lookup","line":11,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["aYiQhcOPTZlphrGiOEnrY"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"# Welcome to Dendron\n\nThis is the root of your dendron vault. If you decide to publish your entire vault, this will be your landing page. You are free to customize any part of this page except the frontmatter on top.\n\n## Lookup\n\nThis section contains useful links to related resources.\n\n- [Getting Started Guide](https://link.dendron.so/6b25)\n- [Discord](https://link.dendron.so/6b23)\n- [Home Page](https://wiki.dendron.so/)\n- [Github](https://link.dendron.so/6b24)\n- [Developer Docs](https://docs.dendron.so/)\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":4,"useFMTitle":true,"useNoteTitleForLink":true,"mermaid":true,"useKatex":true,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true},"site":{"assetsPrefix":"/system-design-notes","copyAssets":true,"siteHierarchies":["root"],"siteRootDir":"docs","siteUrl":"https://mattkuo.github.io","usePrettyRefs":true,"ti